@{FG Shine}Welcome to AmiChannel News@{FG Text}

Hello and welcome to the 12th issue of AmiChannel News.

First of all, I would like to apologize for releaseing the "June" issue in July.
You can blame my nephew because he was born on Friday June, 25th, so I could not
access my beloved Amiga to edit the issue you are reading now.

Before  speaking  about  anything  else,  please let me tell you that this issue
means the first anniversary of the magazine you are reading now. It has not been
easy  to  reach the 12th issue. Although I recieved the help of some friends for
the first two issues, the rest ones have been produced by myself.

But  this magazine is really the result of your support. So far, I have recieved
letters  from  four  readers.  Every  word  of  these  letters  has given me the
necessary  strenght  to  continue to release it. So, thanks Donald, Uno, johnnie
and from Berk Iybar from Turkey. And I apologize because I have not yet answered
your emails. I am currently working hard at my job so I have not time to reply.

And,  it  has  not been easy because things have been hard in the past. Remember
that  this magazine was born after the infamous World of Amiga 98, the date when
the  Amiga  classic  was  stated  as  "dead" by Amiga Inc. We have seen how some
magazines  have  closed  (CU-Amiga),  some  developers have left the Amiga scene
(Vulcan, A.C.T.), ... but the future is really bright.

A  new  magazine (Amigactive) is about to be born from the CU-Amiga's ashes, the
AmigaOS  3.5 is about to be released (by the way, it is going to be premiered in
Australia, congratulations aussies)... And there is a responsible for this: last
name Collas, first name Jim.

I  do  not  know this "guy" personally, but every open letter he writes makes me
feel  as  he  is  just  like another Amigan, he never used an Amiuga though. And
sometimes I think is more "Amigan" than Petro himself ;-)

In these letters, Jim uses repeatedly a word: REVOLUTION. We do not know yet the
exact  features  of the AmigaNG, netiher the first Amiga products to be released
(except  the  OS 3.5 and the dev boxes), but he is planning to manage Amiga (the
company)  in  a  revolutionary way. This "Amiga Advisory Council", whose members
are  going to be some of the Amiga leaders, is a really good idea. For the first
time, the community is going to be a part active of the company.

The  next  issue  of AmiChannel News is going to be released some days after the
World  of  Amiga  99,  to be held in London 24-25 July. I hope to bring you with
all the details of the show.

Let  me  to  finish  this editorial revealing a big secret. A friend of mine who
read  once  one  of  the  AmiChannel  News  editorials,  asked  me  once why the
editorials  had such a weird title (I do not remember what title was). Well, the
explanation  is  very  simple. Forrest Gump used to say that the life was like a
chocolate  box.  I  do not agree with him. Martin Tapper (from the TV show Dream
On)  used  to relate his own experiences with old TV series. In a similar way, I
use songs. As easy as that. Every life could be explained using titles of songs.
In  this  issue, I have used the last hit of Backstreet Boys (BTW, I do not like
their music :-p).

Remember to visit the @{B}SAUG@{UB} website, which is located in:

         @{B}http://www.saug.com/eng/selec.html@{UB}

or you can visit its mirrors located in:

         @{B}http://www.geocities.com/@{UB}

And if you want to contribute to this effort, you can send your articles to:

         @{I}angel@saug.org @{UI}

Thanks for reading and I hope you enjoy this issue.

===============================================================================
