@node not02 "FIRST WIPEOUT 2097 AMIGA SCREENSHOTS"

FIRST WIPEOUT 2097 AMIGA SCREENSHOTS
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Digital Images proudly presents the current state of the Wipeout2097 project for
AMIGA  together  with  the  very  first screenshots out of the current prototype
version  for  AMIGA.  But  finally  the biggest hurdles have been taken, and the
project  makes  really  good progress. Two developers are intensively working on
WO2097 for AMIGA.

Right  now  we  have compiled the game for PPC/WarpUp, and we have an executable
which  actually  works.  The  tracks can be played and most effects seem to work
fine. The game actually runs in fullscreen mode and also in window mode. We will
also  add  the possibility to resize the window on the fly, which will certainly
be an exciting feature, which again will show: 'Only AMIGA makes it possible!'.

Nevertheless  there  is  still  a long way ahead of us. We will need time to add
optimizations  to the engine. Right now the whole AMIGA version is based on 100%
C,  which  of  course makes the game running slower as if it was optimized using
assembler parts. We will make sure to get out as much as possible from the AMIGA
hardware.

Right now there is no sound (neither CD sound nor FX), and the animation playing
stuff  (MPEG)  is  in development. Additionally a lot of finetuning and analysis
have to be done to ensure that the graphics quality gets as good as possible.

These  screenshots  were  taken off the current prototype version of Wipeout2097
for  AMIGA.  These  are  the  very first screenshots of WO2097 AMIGA ever shown.
Enjoy :)

You   can   find  full  size  screenshots  able  to  find  more  screenshots  in
www.digital-images.demon.co.uk
