@node not03 "IBROWSE2: CLOSE TO BE RELEASED"

IBROWSE2: CLOSE TO BE RELEASED
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Some  days  before  Easter  someone  announced that the release of iBrowse 2 was
imminent.  However,  this  wasn't entirely true, iBrowse 2 is currently still in
beta test.

This  process  will take some time because IBrowse 2 adds a lot of new features:
full  JavaScript  1.2  implementation,  HTML  4  support, improved GUI, improved
preferences,  the cache system has been rewritten (it's now even faster and even
easier  to  use),  the  table  parser has been rewritten (it's now lots faster),
spoofing has been implemented, there's external news client support, an improved
URL  completer,  multiple  browsers can be opened in one window (controlled by a
nifty tab system) plus, of course, plug-in support, and more, much more.

Testing  is  going  well and iBrowse 2 is very, very close to being released. In
the meantime, here's a screenshot of one of the new preferences panels. This new
panel implements something that thousands of users asked for, the ability to set
how  iBrowse  displays  individual  websites.  For  example,  you can enable GIF
animations for some sites and disable them for others.
