@node not04 "MICROCODE TO DEVELOP FUSIONPPC AND PCXPPC IF..."

MICROCODE TO DEVELOP FUSIONPPC AND PCXPPC IF...
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Microcode  Solutions have announced that they will develop FusionPPC and PCxPPC,
if  they  get 500 pre-paid orders for each product. The retail price for the PPC
upgrade  modules  is $199.95 for each module. If you pre-pay for either product,
you  will  be  charge  only $149.95. If there are not enough pre-paid orders for
either product, they will not finish that product!

Both  emulations  will  offer  no  more  restriction over the 68K versions, only
enhancements.

PCx PPC

The  PPC  module for PCx will feature full Pentium II processor level emulation,
using dual CPU support. The 68K CPU will handle the video, audio, and other I/O,
while the PPC CPU will be used strictly for x86 emulation/translation.

Initial list of features for PCx PPC:

   * Support for Windows 3.1/95/98
   * Faster all round emulation
   * Improved and enhanced video support, all VESA modes supported
   * Improved Audio

FUSION PPC

Fusion  PPC will bring PowerMac emulation to the Amiga, so you can run Macintosh
native  PowerPC  applications  on your Amiga. There will be an option to use the
68K  CPU to execute 68K instructions instead of allowing the PowerMac to emulate
the 68K CPU (like normal), resulting in dual processor usage.

Initial list of features for Fusion PPC:

   * Support for all current PPC supporting Mac OS versions.
   *  Will  require/support compatible PPC Mac ROM image on release, with future
   support for iMac system CD (ROM-less) targeted.
   *  Use of the 68K CPU to handle 68K CPU instructions, instead of allowing the
   MAC to emulate the 68K CPU.
   * Compatible with current PPC Mac software.
