@node not06 "THE WORLD FOUNDRY NEWS: JUNE UPDATE"

THE WORLD FOUNDRY NEWS: JUNE UPDATE
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Explorer 2260 Update

This  is  what  has  been added (on the design and programming end of things) to
Explorer 2260 in May.

   * 3D editor redesigned and reimplementation started with a focus changed from
   full object creation to editing, texturing and zoning.
   *  Server  architecture  altered,  filesystem  operations  now handled by the
   client unless client and server are not on the same machine.
   * Investigation into a port of the server core to linux underway (with a view
   to allowing multiplayer games to be set up on Linux boxes)
   * Development focus moved to implementation of the 3D engine using Warp3D.
   * Region specific time handling partially implemented.
   *   Hyperspace   calculations  and  Theory  Of  Hyperspace  altered  slightly
   (involving the clearing of a small forest to provide the paper).

Graphical  work  will  be  increasing  in  June  now that school studies are now
finished.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Maim & Mangle Update

Work  has  picked  up  a bit with M&M and the 3d engine is getting nicer as time
goes on with some rather cool features.

These are the new features added to the engine in May:

   * hierichal objs
   * enhanced double buffering routine, it doesn't rely on the ScrollVPort trick
   anymore
   * gouround shading
   * infrared night vision
   * the daylight may vary during battles
   *  general speedup (now it reach 40fps on a 604/180 + CVPPC with a resolution
   of 640x480 15 bit)
   * implemented first fx effects
   * pick/info on units

Features to be added in June:

   * a new gui (maybe based on semi-trasparent floating windows)
   * more fx effects
   * first AI implementation

There  was  also  several  work  on our internal developent tool, M3D editor and
Terrain editor.
