@node not22 "OLAF BARTHEL GIVES SOME DETAILS ABOUT THE OS3.5"

OLAF BARTHEL GIVES SOME DETAILS ABOUT THE OS3.5
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

The  development  of  the  eargely  awaited AMigaOS 3.5 is coming to an end. The
first  beta  versions  are  being shipping now and it is going to be released os
August,  21st  (at  the  same  date  that  "The  Phantom  Menace" is going to be
premiered in Spain).

Olaf  Barthel  has been recently very communicative in the german newsgroups. He
has given some details about the 3.5 icon.library: icons will always contain 1-2
icon  bitmaps for compatibility reasons, the more colorful icon images are saved
in an extended format which packs much better than NewIcons.

Olaf  Barthel  has  pointed  out  that the new 3.5 icon system will be backwards
compatibly  all  the  way down to kickstart 1.0. He has said this wasn't done to
satisfy A1000 users, but rather because he didn't want to modify the icon format
in  a  way  to  make  it  unreadable by all Amigas who don't have 3.5 installed,
especially as that way the OS 3.5 (install) CD would look pretty empty.

The  "browser"  is  only  supposed for reading the online documentation, and the
version of Miami will probably only support one network connection at a time.

Olaf  Barthel  has said the quality "rules" imposed by Amiga for AmigaOS 3.5 are
not meant to restrict the success of the product, but that they rather originate
from  the  fact  that  Amiga  Inc. are unsure and they feel "fear" as far as the
results  of  the  OS  3.5 project are concerned. The cause for these feelings is
that  they  don't know the market and the Amiga community. Only Jim Collas seems
to have understood what problems they caused themselves with this behaviour.

Olaf Barthel has said one idea when chosing the features for OS 3.5 was the need
for  reducing patches, by integrating functionality that is expected nowadays on
the operating system.

Olaf  has said Amiga's goals with the update are to keep a low profile and don't
do anything which might cost too much. The decision that RTG/RTA was not allowed
to  be  part of the update also came from Amiga. However, Olaf has said that one
should  not  under-estimate  the package. He has said that it contains more than
the website or the few previews made believe.
